CodedCharSet.name: CodedCharSet
CodedCharSet.description: A coded character set value that specifies both a set of characters that may be used and an encoding (as one or more octets) that is used to represent the characters in the set. These values are to be used to identify the encoding employed for strings in the MIB where this is not fixed by the MIB.

mltPrtMibVersion.name: mltPrtMibVersion
mltPrtMibVersion.description: The standardization version of MIB implemented in a printer. This indicates the version of the Private Printer MIB that is implemented. There are some mib objects that indicate the Mib Version. (mltSysMibVersion, mltPrtMibVersion, mltScnMibVersion, mltNetMibVersion, mltJmMibVersion) But, the each mib version should be same version. Especially, the each major versions must be same. A string specifying Printer MIB Standard specification version. General form is ##.XX. ## is indicating major revision, and XX is minor revision. Decimal point is ASCII-coded period.

mltPrtCommandTable.name: mltPrtCommandTable
mltPrtCommandTable.description: The table for showing the command information of printer relation. This table must be implemented even if no function in this table are supported by a model.

mltPrtCommandEntry.name: mltPrtCommandEntry
mltPrtCommandEntry.description: An entry exists in this table for each device entry in the hostmib device table whose type is 'printer'.

mltPrtCommandOnline.name: mltPrtCommandOnline
mltPrtCommandOnline.description: Indicate printer online or offline. If printer has no online button, this value should be notSupported (0) as read-only.

mltPrtCommandJobCancel.name: mltPrtCommandJobCancel
mltPrtCommandJobCancel.description: Command of cancel job. If printer has not job cancel function, this value should be notSupported (0) as read-only. In normal condition, this value should be notCancel (1). If canceling job, set this object jobCancel (2).

mltPrtCommandJobProceed.name: mltPrtCommandJobProceed
mltPrtCommandJobProceed.description: Command of proceeds. If printer has not proceed function, this value should be notSupported (0) as read-only. In normal condition, this value should be notProceed (1). If proceeding job, set this object proceed (2).

mltPrtPrintPageTable.name: mltPrtPrintPageTable
mltPrtPrintPageTable.description: A table of printable configuration print. If a printer does not support print the test pages from network access, this table needs not to be implemented.

mltPrtPrintPageEntry.name: mltPrtPrintPageEntry
mltPrtPrintPageEntry.description: Information about printer's configuration prints. Entries may exist in the table for each device index whose device type is 'printer'.

mltPrtPrintPageIndex.name: mltPrtPrintPageIndex
mltPrtPrintPageIndex.description: Index for uniquely distinguishing the page held within a printer. Although the value of index depends on an implementation,

mltPrtPrintPageName.name: mltPrtPrintPageName
mltPrtPrintPageName.description: The name of the page, which can be printed. The value that should be implemented depends on an implementation of a model and it should be common with a manual etc.

mltPrtPrintCommand.name: mltPrtPrintCommand
mltPrtPrintCommand.description: Command of print page. In normal condition , this value should be supported (1). If print page, set this object print (2).

mltPrtSysConfigTable.name: mltPrtSysConfigTable
mltPrtSysConfigTable.description: A table of configurations for printer. This table must be implemented even if no functions in this table are supported.

mltPrtSysConfigEntry.name: mltPrtSysConfigEntry
mltPrtSysConfigEntry.description: An entry exists in this table for each device entry in the hostmib device table whose type is 'printer'.

mltPrtJobLanguage.name: mltPrtJobLanguage
mltPrtJobLanguage.description: Configuration printer job language. Only in the case that a printer has a function of setting(changing) this default printer language, this object is implemented as RW. In the other case, this object should be implemented as RO. In case of PCL/PS printer, default value is Auto(0). If necessary, PCL(1)/PS(2) is changeable. In case of printer has only one interpreter (PCL or PS), this object should be pcl(1) or ps (2) as RO. In case of GDI printer, this value is GDI(3) (RO).

mltPrtPowerSave.name: mltPrtPowerSave
mltPrtPowerSave.description: Timer value setting before the power save mode is asserted. Unit is minutes. If '0' is selected, the controller doesn't enter Power Save mode. If this value is -1, printer doesn't support power save mode. If out of spec value is set, Error is returned.

mltPrtAutoContinue.name: mltPrtAutoContinue
mltPrtAutoContinue.description: The setting whether printing will automatically recover or not when an Error or Caution occurred. If a device support only the value of 1(off) and 2(ac0Sec), this implementation is allowed.

mltPrtPaperTimeOut.name: mltPrtPaperTimeOut
mltPrtPaperTimeOut.description: Setting which decides whether automatic recover should be proceed or not when an error related to paper occurred.

mltPrtPsErrorPrint.name: mltPrtPsErrorPrint
mltPrtPsErrorPrint.description: The setting whether the printer prints PostScript Error Page when PostScript Error occurred during job processing. About PS error, since it is the function of a printer controller, all the devices with PS should be implemented If a device has no PostScript interpreter, this value should be always notSupported(0) as RO.

mltPrtPrintConfigTable.name: mltPrtPrintConfigTable
mltPrtPrintConfigTable.description: A table of configurations for printer. This table must be implemented even if no functions in this table are supported.

mltPrtPrintConfigEntry.name: mltPrtPrintConfigEntry
mltPrtPrintConfigEntry.description: An entry exists in this table for each device entry in the hostmib device table whose type is 'printer'

mltPrtCopies.name: mltPrtCopies
mltPrtCopies.description: The number of printing copies. If set value is over limit, printer should return error. About device which has no PCL interpreter, This value should be -1, because of no default copies setting.

mltPrtPaperSize.name: mltPrtPaperSize
mltPrtPaperSize.description: Paper size of printing. The value of the mltPaperSizeIndex corresponding to the current paper size. About device which has no PCL interpreter, This value should be -1, because of no default paper size setting.

mltPrtPaperSource.name: mltPrtPaperSource
mltPrtPaperSource.description: Feeders for printing. The value of prtInputIndex corresponding to the default input sub-unit: that is, this object selects the default source of input media. If value is 0, this means 'Auto'. About device which has no PCL interpreter, This value should be -1, because of no default paper source setting.

mltPrtFineArt.name: mltPrtFineArt
mltPrtFineArt.description: Smooting setting. If printer has no smoothing function, this value should be notSupported(0) and RO. If printer supports only On/Off , this value should be on(1) or offSwitch(2). If printer supports 4 steps, this value should be dark(3), medium(4), light(5) and offStep(6).

mltPrtTonerSave.name: mltPrtTonerSave
mltPrtTonerSave.description: Toner saving setting. If printer is not supporting toner save function, this value should be notSupported(0) and RO. If printer is supporting toner save function, this value should be on(1) or off(2) and RW.

mltPrtPclFontTable.name: mltPrtPclFontTable
mltPrtPclFontTable.description: This table shows PCL font information of printer has. Since it is a function peculiar to PCL, it is not necessary to implement this table in the device in which PCL is not installed or PCL font management function is not installed.

mltPrtPclFontEntry.name: mltPrtPclFontEntry
mltPrtPclFontEntry.description: Information about printer's PCL fonts. Entries may exist in the table for each device index whose device type is 'printer'.

mltPrtPclFontIndex.name: mltPrtPclFontIndex
mltPrtPclFontIndex.description: A unique value used to identify this entry.

mltPrtPclFontNumber.name: mltPrtPclFontNumber
mltPrtPclFontNumber.description: The number of PCL Font. The number for managing the font, which a printer holds inside.

mltPrtPclFontSource.name: mltPrtPclFontSource
mltPrtPclFontSource.description: The information of a place that PCL font exists.

mltPrtPsFontTable.name: mltPrtPsFontTable
mltPrtPsFontTable.description: This table shows PostScript font information of printer has. Since it is a function peculiar to PS, it is not necessary to implement this table in the device in which PS is not installed.

mltPrtPsFontEntry.name: mltPrtPsFontEntry
mltPrtPsFontEntry.description: Information about printer's PS fonts. Entries may exist in the table for each device index whose device type is 'printer'.

mltPrtPsFontIndex.name: mltPrtPsFontIndex
mltPrtPsFontIndex.description: A unique value used to identify this entry.

mltPrtPsFontNumber.name: mltPrtPsFontNumber
mltPrtPsFontNumber.description: The number of PS Font. This number is used in order to administrate printer's fonts. If a printer does not manage this number, this value should be implemented same as mltPrtPsFontIndex.

mltPrtPsFontSource.name: mltPrtPsFontSource
mltPrtPsFontSource.description: The information of a place that PS font exists

mltPrtSymbolSetTable.name: mltPrtSymbolSetTable
mltPrtSymbolSetTable.description: This table shows symbol sets a printer has. If no function in this table is supported by a device, this table needs not to be implemented.

mltPrtSymbolSetEntry.name: mltPrtSymbolSetEntry
mltPrtSymbolSetEntry.description: Information about printer's symbol sets. Entries may exist in the table for each device index whose device type is 'printer'.

mltPrtSymbolSetIndex.name: mltPrtSymbolSetIndex
mltPrtSymbolSetIndex.description: A unique value used to identify this entry.

mltPrtCharSetID.name: mltPrtCharSetID
mltPrtCharSetID.description: The ID of Code CharSet. Refer to the following URL that IANA administrates regarding character code sets: http://www.iana.org/assignments/character-sets

mltPrtPaperSizeTable.name: mltPrtPaperSizeTable
mltPrtPaperSizeTable.description: A table of the printer selectable paper sizes. Even if a printer can not recognize the supportable paper, one object ('unknown' or 'other') must be loaded at least.

mltPrtPaperSizeEntry.name: mltPrtPaperSizeEntry
mltPrtPaperSizeEntry.description: An entry exists in this table for each device entry in the hostmib device table whose type is 'printer'

mltPaperSizeIndex.name: mltPaperSizeIndex
mltPaperSizeIndex.description: A unique value used to identify this entry.

mltPaperSizeName.name: mltPaperSizeName
mltPaperSizeName.description: The name of paper size. e.g., letter, legal, A4, B5 etc.

mltPaperFeedDir.name: mltPaperFeedDir
mltPaperFeedDir.description: This value shows paper feeding orientation.

mltPrtRemotePanelButtonTable.name: mltPrtRemotePanelButtonTable
mltPrtRemotePanelButtonTable.description: A table of printer's remote operational panel button.

mltPrtRemotePanelButtonEntry.name: mltPrtRemotePanelButtonEntry
mltPrtRemotePanelButtonEntry.description: An entry exists in this table for each device entry in the hostmib device table whose type is `printer'

mltPrtPanelButtonIndex.name: mltPrtPanelButtonIndex
mltPrtPanelButtonIndex.description: A unique value used by the operational panel button to identify table

mltPrtPanelButtonPush.name: mltPrtPanelButtonPush
mltPrtPanelButtonPush.description: This value indicates panel button status, and make pushing button. noAction (0) -- indicate steady. push (1) -- To set 1 means push panel button. longPush (2) -- To set 2 means push button long time. shiftPush (3) -- To set 3 means push panel bottom and shift button same time.

mltPrtPanelButtonDescr.name: mltPrtPanelButtonDescr
mltPrtPanelButtonDescr.description: An explanation of panel button function etc.

mltSysMibVersion.name: mltSysMibVersion
mltSysMibVersion.description: The version information of Standard MIB specification. This indicates the version of the Private System MIB which is implemented. General form is AA.BC. AA is indicating major revision, and B and C is minor revision. Decimal point is ASCII-coded period.

mltSysPriorityDevice.name: mltSysPriorityDevice
mltSysPriorityDevice.description: This object shows the function which operates with highest priority in a system. When it can set up by user choice etc., it should be RW. If setup change is impossible from MIB, the implementation of RO is acceptable. There is no function with highest priority or no preference order of function, implement RO as 0.

mltSysCurrentDateTime.name: mltSysCurrentDateTime
mltSysCurrentDateTime.description: Time, which is set in the system and specifies by DateAndTime If not having a clock function, implement 0x00 in all Bytes.

mltSysContactSiteName.name: mltSysContactSiteName
mltSysContactSiteName.description: The name of a support contact for system. If device cannot support this object, device should be implement '-' as read-only

mltSysContactInfo.name: mltSysContactInfo
mltSysContactInfo.description: Explanation of a support contact for system. Default value shall be a blank, and a service person or a user shall input it. If device cannot support this object, device should be implement '-' as read-only

mltSysProductHelpURL.name: mltSysProductHelpURL
mltSysProductHelpURL.description: URL of the support contact for system. If device cannot support this object, device should be implement '-' as read-only

mltSysCorpURL.name: mltSysCorpURL
mltSysCorpURL.description: URL of the company which provides a system. If device cannot support this object, device should be implement '-' as read-only

mltSysSuppliesInfo.name: mltSysSuppliesInfo
mltSysSuppliesInfo.description: A telephone number or E-mail addresses for the supplies and accessories, etc. In the support contact in which a system has. Default shall be a blank, and a service person or a user shall input it. If device cannot support this object, device should be implement '-' as read-only

mltSysVersionTable.name: mltSysVersionTable
mltSysVersionTable.description: The table for showing ROM and F/W version in which a system has.

mltSysVersionEntry.name: mltSysVersionEntry
mltSysVersionEntry.description: The version information of FW or ROM.

mltSysVersionIndex.name: mltSysVersionIndex
mltSysVersionIndex.description: Index for uniquely showing the version information in which a system has. The number and the order of index depends on an implementation of a model. Implement the maximum number of index of ROM and F/W which is possible to detect/display, regardless of the availability of installation of Option etc. The number of indexes to hold shall be always fixed regardless of the option installation state.

mltSysVerName.name: mltSysVerName
mltSysVerName.description: The name of the function which shows a version. For example, 'MSC/Panel ROM Version', 'Printer ROM Version', etc.

mltSysVersionCode.name: mltSysVersionCode
mltSysVersionCode.description: The version of ROM and F/W. It shall be written by 15 or less characters. '[Product Code(4)]-[Block Code(2)][Stage Code(1)] [Specification Code(1)]-[Change Management Code(2)] -[Shipment Destination Code(2)]' supports. For corresponding to the other written methods, it was made into the maximum 31 characters, on the definition. When the value cannot acquire although index is set by Option etc., display '-' (hyphen).

mltSysVerDescr.name: mltSysVerDescr
mltSysVerDescr.description: Explanation of a version. As for the contents to indicate, depends on an implementation of a model. However, since not supporting this object is not acceptable, implement Null (Zero-Length) at least.

mltSysCompConfigID.name: mltSysCompConfigID
mltSysCompConfigID.description: Shows the ID by the combination of the structure of Device. A project should prepare ID which is worth for the number of combination, such as Option. If system has no option or cannot detect option installed, this value should be always 0.

mltSysInputTrayTable.name: mltSysInputTrayTable
mltSysInputTrayTable.description: The table for showing the information of Input tray that is installed in a system. As a principle, the un-acquirable information shall be displayed if there is only prtInputTable, and this table is premised on that PrinterMIB is being implemented. It shall display about InputTray which is installed like prtInputTable. If a system does not have a printer engine (has no input tray and no PrinterMIB), this table does not need to implement.

mltSysInputTrayEntry.name: mltSysInputTrayEntry
mltSysInputTrayEntry.description: The information of paper input tray.

mltSysInputTrayIndex.name: mltSysInputTrayIndex
mltSysInputTrayIndex.description: Index for showing InputTray in a system. Index depends on the state of the implementation of a model, and shall be taken the amount which is worth for the number of InputTray in the order from 1.

mltSysInputTrayRefIndex.name: mltSysInputTrayRefIndex
mltSysInputTrayRefIndex.description: The value of prtInputIndex of a tray which mltSysInputTrayIndex shows.

mltSysInputTrayName.name: mltSysInputTrayName
mltSysInputTrayName.description: The name of InputTray. Default value depends on a model. In principle, use the name unified by DriverUI. Set of the character string up to 15 characters shall be possible. implementation of RO is also accepted when there are capacity restrictions of NVRAM. Since this item is the value used when a user does a remote management, it is not necessary to link it with a setup of a printer engine. SNMP agent holds value, and should just provide the convenience to the user who remote accesses.

mltSysInputTrayCapacitySence.name: mltSysInputTrayCapacitySence
mltSysInputTrayCapacitySence.description: This item shows the detection method of paper residual quantity, and is used for distinction of the value displayed in prtInputCurrentLevel. The details of a residual quantity display are indicated to prtInputCurrentLevel.

mltSysInputTraySpecialPaper.name: mltSysInputTraySpecialPaper
mltSysInputTraySpecialPaper.description: Shows the media type of InputTray. If this value is RW and when a setup is changed by MIB, it shall be reflected in a setup of a printer engine. In a unavoidable case, the access way may be RO.

mltSysInputTrayPaperAttribute.name: mltSysInputTrayPaperAttribute
mltSysInputTrayPaperAttribute.description: Shows the paper attribute of InputTray. If this value is RW and when a setup is changed by MIB, it shall be reflected in a setup of a printer engine. In a unavoidable case, the access way may be RO.

mltSysOutputTrayTable.name: mltSysOutputTrayTable
mltSysOutputTrayTable.description: The table for showing the information of OutputTray relation in a system. Index shall be mltSysOutputTrayIndex. This table is for displaying the tray information of OutputOption (Finisher), and shall not include the function information of Finisher. If a system does not have a printer engine (has no output tray and no PrinterMIB), this table may not be implemented.

mltSysOutputTrayEntry.name: mltSysOutputTrayEntry
mltSysOutputTrayEntry.description: The information of paper output tray.

mltSysOutputTrayIndex.name: mltSysOutputTrayIndex
mltSysOutputTrayIndex.description: Index for showing OutputTray in a system. Index depends on the implementation of a model, and shall be taken the amount which is worth for the number of Output in the order from 1. In principle, when the top tray is set as 1, index shall be increased in progress of going to the lower part. As for the middle processing tray that does not become papers' final output destination, is not treated as OutputTray.

mltSysOutputTrayRefIndex.name: mltSysOutputTrayRefIndex
mltSysOutputTrayRefIndex.description: Value of prtOutputIndex of the tray which mltSysOutputTrayIndex shows.

mltSysOutputTrayDefaultName.name: mltSysOutputTrayDefaultName
mltSysOutputTrayDefaultName.description: The name of OutputTray. Unify with the notation of a manual or a driver.

mltSysOutputTrayNickName.name: mltSysOutputTrayNickName
mltSysOutputTrayNickName.description: The name of OutputTray in which a user can set up. In MailBin, use it in order to indicate a user's name, etc. which each Tray set up. The recommendation default is the same as mltSysOutputTrayDefaultName. Set of the character string up to 15 characters shall be possible, and neither retrenchment of the number of characters which can be written in, nor implementation of RO shall be accepted. However, the implementation of RO is accepted only to the thing without MailBin as OutputOption. Moreover, being reflected in the display screen of a printer driver is desirable. Since this item is the value used when a user does a remote management, it is not necessary to link it with a setup of a printer engine. SNMP agent holds value, and should just provide the convenience to the user who remote accesses. If device cannot support this function, this object should be '-' as ReadOnly.

mltSysOutputTrayType.name: mltSysOutputTrayType
mltSysOutputTrayType.description: Shows the type of tray in OutputTray. This is an item for judging whether it is MailBin, and it is used in order to judge whether the writing of NickName should be possible.

mltSysSupportedCounterType.name: mltSysSupportedCounterType
mltSysSupportedCounterType.description: Shows the type of a counter installed in a system. The counter which a system has can specify by referring to this. Displays the counter to support with Bitmap and shows the supporting counter by the total. Bit Value CounterType --- ----- --------------- 0 1 GeneralCounter 1 2 PrintFunctionCounter 2 4 SendFunctionCounter 3 8 PapersSizeCounter 4 16 DivCounter 5 32 TonerLifeCounter It becomes 63 when implementing all the counters.

mltSysDuplexCountMode.name: mltSysDuplexCountMode
mltSysDuplexCountMode.description: Sets up whether Duplex printing is counted two times to TotalCounter at the time. This setup is reflected to all TotalCounters. This object may be implemented with RO access. If a system doesn't have this setting (e.g. printer), the value of the static count mode (1 or 2) must be implemented. Basically this value must not be '0'. This is also applied to mtSysLargeSizeCountMode and mltSysLargeSizeMode same.

mltSysLargeSizeCountMode.name: mltSysLargeSizeCountMode
mltSysLargeSizeCountMode.description: Sets up whether LargeSize is counted two times to TotalCounter at the time. This setup is reflected to all TotalCounters. This object may be implemented with RO access. This setting is the item of a service choice. A setup of a service choice is reflected to this object. Also enable operation from PageScope. Management of the access rights supports by PageScope side.

mltSysLargeSizeType.name: mltSysLargeSizeType
mltSysLargeSizeType.description: Sets up the type of paper counted as LargeSize. noLargeSize(0): indicates that the count of LargeSize is not performed or not detect large size type. typeA(1): For US is 11x17, For EU is A3, For Japan is A3. typeB(2): For US is 11x17, For EU is A3/B4, For Japan is A3/B4. typeC(3): For US is 11x17/11x14/8.5x14, For EU is A3/B4, For Japan A3/B4. This object may be implemented with RO access. The choice item of EP-NET. Also enable operation from PageScope.

mltSysColorCountSupportType.name: mltSysColorCountSupportType
mltSysColorCountSupportType.description: It is shown what kind of counter by the color is supported. The color counter which a device supports can be specified by referring to this. Displays the type of counter to support with Bitmap and shows the supporting counter by the total. The type counter that is shown in here shall be held by the color-related counter. Bit Value CounterType --- ----- ----------------- 0 1 reserved 1 2 bw --The monochrome counter --in a color machine 2 4 fourColor (4c) --Full color -- (All of C, M, Y, and K are used) 3 8 threeColor (3c) --Monochrome color --(monochrome is taken out using -- three colors of C, M, and Y) 4 16 cmy --CMY: (using any 1 color of C/M/Y) 5 32 rgb --RGB: (using three colors of CMY) 6 64 monoColor --The total of 3C, CMY, and RGB 7 128 paperPath --PaperPath counter

mltSysTotalCount.name: mltSysTotalCount
mltSysTotalCount.description: The total print count of a system. Displays the total of Copy, Print, and Receiving Job. About the count method of Duplex and LargeSize, it depends on a setup. A count shall be an output count. About a color machine, it shall be the total of all color classifications.

mltSysLargeSizeCount.name: mltSysLargeSizeCount
mltSysLargeSizeCount.description: The total print count of LargeSize paper. About the type of LargeSize, it depends on a setup of mltSysLargeSizeType. When the setup of mltSysLargeSizeType is noCount(0), this counter always shall be -1. In addition, also in the system without A4 machine, etc., this counter should be -1.

mltSysDuplexCount.name: mltSysDuplexCount
mltSysDuplexCount.description: The total print count of Duplex (back). In the system without Duplex mechanism, it should be -1.

mltSysLargeDuplexCount.name: mltSysLargeDuplexCount
mltSysLargeDuplexCount.description: The total print count of LargeSize, and also Duplex (back). About the type of LargeSize, it depends on a setup of mltSysLargeSizeType. When the setup of mltSysLargeSizeType is noCount(0), this counter always shall be -1. In addition, in the system of A4 machine or in the system without Duplex, this counter always should be -1.

mltSysSendTotalCount.name: mltSysSendTotalCount
mltSysSendTotalCount.description: Total count scaned as a transmitting function in the system. It shall be the total of mltSysSendScanCount. In the device without Scan function, it always shall be -1.

mltSysTotalJamCount.name: mltSysTotalJamCount
mltSysTotalJamCount.description: The number of times of Jam occurred in the system. It shall be the total of all Jam counters. (including ADF jams).

mltSysTotalTroubleCount.name: mltSysTotalTroubleCount
mltSysTotalTroubleCount.description: The number of times of Trouble (FatalError) occurred in the system. It shall be the total of all Trouble counters.

mltSysPrintFunctionCounterTable.name: mltSysPrintFunctionCounterTable
mltSysPrintFunctionCounterTable.description: The table for showing the counter by the color and function. In the monochrome machine of a single function, it is not necessary to implement.

mltSysPrintFunctionCounterEntry.name: mltSysPrintFunctionCounterEntry
mltSysPrintFunctionCounterEntry.description: The counters of color and print functions.

mltSysPrintFunctionColorIndex.name: mltSysPrintFunctionColorIndex
mltSysPrintFunctionColorIndex.description: Index for showing the color in the counter by color/function. By the color, index shall be attached in the order of the following. No. Function -------------------- 1 BW 2 4C 3 3C 4 CMY 5 RGB 6 MonoColor

mltSysPrintFunctionIndex.name: mltSysPrintFunctionIndex
mltSysPrintFunctionIndex.description: Index for showing the function in the counter by color/function. By the function, index shall be attached in the order of the following. No. Function -------------------- 1 copy 2 printer 3 received Job 4 fax received Job 5 reportPrint Although classifying into printer/receive Job/fax receive job as a printing function is recommended, the implementation of multiple counting as a printer function is also accepted.

mltSysPrintFunctionColorType.name: mltSysPrintFunctionColorType
mltSysPrintFunctionColorType.description: Shows the color mode in the counter by color/function.

mltSysPrintFunctionType.name: mltSysPrintFunctionType
mltSysPrintFunctionType.description: Shows the function in the counter by color/function. Although classifying into printer/receive Job/fax receive job as a printing function is recommended, the implementation of multiple counting as a printer function is also accepted.

mltSysPrintFunctionTotalCount.name: mltSysPrintFunctionTotalCount
mltSysPrintFunctionTotalCount.description: The total print count in a specified function. About the count method, complies with GeneralCounter

mltSysPrintFunctionDuplexCount.name: mltSysPrintFunctionDuplexCount
mltSysPrintFunctionDuplexCount.description: The print count of Duplex (back) in a specified function. The print count of the LargeSize paper in a specified function. About the count method, complies with GeneralCounter.

mltSysPrintFunctionLargeSizeCount.name: mltSysPrintFunctionLargeSizeCount
mltSysPrintFunctionLargeSizeCount.description: The print count of the LargeSize paper in a specified function. About the count method, complies with GeneralCounter.

mltSysPrintFunctionLargeDuplexCount.name: mltSysPrintFunctionLargeDuplexCount
mltSysPrintFunctionLargeDuplexCount.description: The print count of LargeSize and Duplex (back) in a specified function. About the count method, complies with GeneralCounter.

mltSysSizeCounterTable.name: mltSysSizeCounterTable
mltSysSizeCounterTable.description: The table of the counter by the paper sizes (types). The model which supports plural paper sizes has to implement. Regardless of shipment destination, having a counter to all the paper sizes that can be printed is recommended. By implementation, implementing different size counter by shipment destination is also accepted. It shall also have index by the functions so that it can correspond to the counter by sizes by the functions.

mltSysSizeCounterEntry.name: mltSysSizeCounterEntry
mltSysSizeCounterEntry.description: The information of paper size counters.

mltSysSizeFunctionIndex.name: mltSysSizeFunctionIndex
mltSysSizeFunctionIndex.description: Index for showing the function which becomes the count object in the counter by paper sizes. Although Index shall be attached in the order of the following by the function, having Index by fixation shall not require. No. Function -------------------- 1 Total

mltSysSizeTypeIndex.name: mltSysSizeTypeIndex
mltSysSizeTypeIndex.description: Index for showing the paper which becomes the count object in the counter by paper sizes. Only the type of corresponding paper shall be taken in the order from 1. Using fixed index for every paper does not require.

mltSysSizeFunction.name: mltSysSizeFunction
mltSysSizeFunction.description: Shows the function which becomes the count object in the counter by paper size.

mltSysSizeType.name: mltSysSizeType
mltSysSizeType.description: Shows the paper which becomes the count object in the counter by paper sizes.

mltSysSizeCount.name: mltSysSizeCount
mltSysSizeCount.description: The number of print of the specified function and specified size, media type, or attribute.

mltSysTonerLifeCounterTable.name: mltSysTonerLifeCounterTable
mltSysTonerLifeCounterTable.description: The table of toner life counter.

mltSysTonerLifeCounterEntry.name: mltSysTonerLifeCounterEntry
mltSysTonerLifeCounterEntry.description: The information of toner life counters.

mltSysTonerTypeIndex.name: mltSysTonerTypeIndex
mltSysTonerTypeIndex.description: Index for Toner used as the count object in TonerLife counter being shown.

mltSysTonerType.name: mltSysTonerType
mltSysTonerType.description: Toner used as the count object in TonerLife counter is shown.

mltTonerTypeCount.name: mltTonerTypeCount
mltTonerTypeCount.description: TonerLife count. This is used for calculation of Coverage, by the amount of Toner consumption, etc. by counting Dot number used for every Toner. 1unit is 2M Dots.

mltNetMibVersion.name: mltNetMibVersion
mltNetMibVersion.description: The standardization version of MIB implemented in Network. This indicates the version of the Private Network MIB. General form is AA.BC. AA is indicating major revision, and B and C is minor revision. Decimal point is ASCII-coded period.

mltNetGeneralTable.name: mltNetGeneralTable
mltNetGeneralTable.description: Table for showing the general information of Network relation.

mltNetGeneralIndex.name: mltNetGeneralIndex
mltNetGeneralIndex.description: Index for showing NetworkInterface installed to a device. Basically, it shall take the same value with ifIndex.

mltNetFirmVersion.name: mltNetFirmVersion
mltNetFirmVersion.description: Shows the FW version of NetworkInterface. Write it as ##.xx. ## shall be a major version and xx shall be a minor version. If there is no original FW of NetworkInterface, implement character strings of '-' (hyphen).

mltNetHardwareAddress.name: mltNetHardwareAddress
mltNetHardwareAddress.description: MAC address of NetworkInterface. (Hardware address) In the device of our company, it was made into RW since MAC address needs to be written at the time of shipment. Implement as RO when the writing of MAC address is unnecessary. Moreover, in a management tool side, be sure to handle it as RO.

mltNetSerialNumber.name: mltNetSerialNumber
mltNetSerialNumber.description: The serial number of NetworkInterface. Implement '-' (hyphen) in the device without a serial number. In the device of our company, it was made into RW since serial number may need to be written at the time of shipment. Implement as RO when the writing of serial number is unnecessary. Moreover, in a management tool side, be sure to handle it as RO.

mltNetSupportedConnector.name: mltNetSupportedConnector
mltNetSupportedConnector.description: An integer bitmap value specifying network connector information. Each bit in the integer is defined as follows. bit Value Connector --- ----- --------- 0 1 Reserved 1 2 Ethernet AUI -- 10Base5 2 4 Ethernet BNC -- 10Base2 3 8 Ethernet RJ45 -- 10/100BaseT 4 16 Ethernet Fiber -- 10/100BaseF 5 32 Reserved 6 64 Reserved 7 128 TokenRing STP(DB-15) 8 256 TokenRing UTP(RJ-45) 9 512 TokenRing Fiber 10 1024 Reserved 11 2048 wirelessA -- 802.11a 12 4096 wirelessB -- 802.11b 13 8132 blueTooth 14 16364 ieee1394 -- IP over IEEE1394

mltNetCurrentConnector.name: mltNetCurrentConnector
mltNetCurrentConnector.description: Shows the connector that is working on NetworkInterface.

mltNetSpeedConfig.name: mltNetSpeedConfig
mltNetSpeedConfig.description: Sets up the speed of NetworkInterface. Refer to ifSpeed for checking the present speed of operation. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement a current set value with RO access.

mltNetIfDescr.name: mltNetIfDescr
mltNetIfDescr.description: Explanation of NetworkInterface. Shows the type of port and the version information. The name to indicate is determined at Project side and implementation of NullString is not accepted. Even if a device have a no description about this, '-' need to be implemented.

mltNetProtocolTable.name: mltNetProtocolTable
mltNetProtocolTable.description: The table for showing the protocol information which NetworkInterface supports.

mltNetProtocolIfIndex.name: mltNetProtocolIfIndex
mltNetProtocolIfIndex.description: Index for showing NetworkInterface that a system has. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetProtocolIndex.name: mltNetProtocolIndex
mltNetProtocolIndex.description: Index for uniquely showing the protocol which a system supports. Index shall be assigned in the following order is recommended. No. Protocol -------------------- 1 TCP/IP 2 NetWare(IPX/SPX) 3 AppleTalk 4 SMB

mltNetProtocolType.name: mltNetProtocolType
mltNetProtocolType.description: Shows the type of supporting protocol.

mltNetProtocolDescr.name: mltNetProtocolDescr
mltNetProtocolDescr.description: Description that shows a protocol. Although the value to indicate shall depend on an implementation, the general protocol name, such as 'TCP/IP', 'NetWare', etc., shall be indicated in principle. Implementation of Null is not accepted.

mltNetProtocolVer.name: mltNetProtocolVer
mltNetProtocolVer.description: The version of the implemented protocol stack. Implement '-' (hyphen) when there is no version notation. Implementation of Null is not accepted.

mltNetProtocolOnOff.name: mltNetProtocolOnOff
mltNetProtocolOnOff.description: Sets up a states display of On and Off of the function of each protocol. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement a current set value with RO access.

mltNetCommandTable.name: mltNetCommandTable
mltNetCommandTable.description: The table for showing the command information which NetworkInterface supports.

mltNetCommandEntry.name: mltNetCommandEntry
mltNetCommandEntry.description: The information of command for network interface.

mltNetCommandIfIndex.name: mltNetCommandIfIndex
mltNetCommandIfIndex.description: Index for uniquely showing the destination of command. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetCommandReset.name: mltNetCommandReset
mltNetCommandReset.description: The command that performs independent reset of NetworkInterface. When reset(2) is set, an agent side shall surely return Reply. Implementation that performs Reset immediately without returning Reply is not accepted. Return Reply of an error, when Reset command is invalid. After reset(2) is set, about the timing which is actually performing Reset depends on an implementation, and it shall not be defined in MIB.

mltNetCommandDefault.name: mltNetCommandDefault
mltNetCommandDefault.description: The command for returning a setup about NetworkInterface to FactoryDefault. When resetToDefault(2) is set, an agent side shall surely return Reply. In principle, when resetToDefault(2) is set, about the timing in which the setup returns to default depends on an implementation and it does not define in MIB.

mltNetCommandPrintNicConfig.name: mltNetCommandPrintNicConfig
mltNetCommandPrintNicConfig.description: The command for making it perform the output of ConfigPage which Network Interface has at the time of normal operation. Independent ConfigPage of two or more kinds of Network is not considered.

mltNetCommandStartupConfig.name: mltNetCommandStartupConfig
mltNetCommandStartupConfig.description: The command that sets up the availability of the output of ConfigPage of NetworkInterface at the time of starting. Independent StartupPage of two or more kinds of Network is not considered.

mltNetCommandDownLoad.name: mltNetCommandDownLoad
mltNetCommandDownLoad.description: The command that sets up the mode that updates FW of NetworkInterface. Since this setup needs to operate with Admin authority, do not perform both display and writing at the management tool side.

mltNetSnmpCommTable.name: mltNetSnmpCommTable
mltNetSnmpCommTable.description: The table for showing the information of Community of SNMP which a system has. In addition, Community name shall be the common to the whole system on the premise, and shall not have independent Community for every NetworkInterface. In having Community independently by Intelligent NIC etc., it shall have NetworkMIB independently to each and is not managed by unified agent.

mltNetSnmpCommIndex.name: mltNetSnmpCommIndex
mltNetSnmpCommIndex.description: Index for identifying each SNMP community. Although about Community number to support, Community name, and each access rights are dependent on an implementation, having the following three Communities is recommended. public (RO) private (RW) admin (RW) It shall be indispensable at least to have public (RW) or to have the two of public (RO) and private (RW).

mltNetSnmpCommName.name: mltNetSnmpCommName
mltNetSnmpCommName.description: Community name of SNMP. Having the above-mentioned name as default is recommended. This item does not accept the implementation of RO. Community name has to be changeable. But if Community name can not be changeable, 'public' or 'private' is recommended to be implemented as Community name with RO access.

mltNetSnmpCommAccessRight.name: mltNetSnmpCommAccessRight
mltNetSnmpCommAccessRight.description: Shows the access rights of SNMP community. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement a current set value with RO access.

mltNetSnmpTrapTable.name: mltNetSnmpTrapTable
mltNetSnmpTrapTable.description: The table for showing the information of destination of Trap of SNMP. When it does not have Trap function of SNMP, this Table does not need to implement.

mltNetSnmpTrapIfIndex.name: mltNetSnmpTrapIfIndex
mltNetSnmpTrapIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely showing the NetworkInterface which becomes the sender of Trap. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetSnmpTrapIndex.name: mltNetSnmpTrapIndex
mltNetSnmpTrapIndex.description: The index for uniquely showing the destination of Trap. In Default, it shall have at least one TrapAddress in a Table.

mltNetSnmpTrapCommunity.name: mltNetSnmpTrapCommunity
mltNetSnmpTrapCommunity.description: Community name at the time of transmitting Trap. In Default, it shall have public. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetSnmpTrapIpAddress.name: mltNetSnmpTrapIpAddress
mltNetSnmpTrapIpAddress.description: IP address of Trap destination. It shall be 255.255.255.255 (BroadCast) in Default. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetSnmpTrapIpxAddress.name: mltNetSnmpTrapIpxAddress
mltNetSnmpTrapIpxAddress.description: IPX address of the destination of Trap. It shall be 'FFFFFFFF:FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF' in Default. When it does not have Trap transmitting function in IPX, the character string of '-' (hyphen) shall be displayed. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetSnmpTrapOnOff.name: mltNetSnmpTrapOnOff
mltNetSnmpTrapOnOff.description: On/Off of transmission of Trap is controlled. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetTcpipGeneralTable.name: mltNetTcpipGeneralTable
mltNetTcpipGeneralTable.description: Table with the basic information of TCP/IP relation which NetworkInterface has.

mltNetTcpipIfIndex.name: mltNetTcpipIfIndex
mltNetTcpipIfIndex.description: Index for uniquely showing NetworkInterface which IP address is set up. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetTcpipDefault.name: mltNetTcpipDefault
mltNetTcpipDefault.description: The command that returns all setup about TCP/IP to FactoryDefault. When resetToDefault(2) is set, an agent side shall surely return Reply. In principle, when resetToDefault(2) is set, about the timing in which the setup returns to default depends on an implementation and it does not define in MIB.

mltNetTcpipAddress.name: mltNetTcpipAddress
mltNetTcpipAddress.description: IP address of NetworkInterface. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetTcpipSubnet.name: mltNetTcpipSubnet
mltNetTcpipSubnet.description: Subnet mask of NetworkInterface. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetTcpipGateway.name: mltNetTcpipGateway
mltNetTcpipGateway.description: DefaultGateway of NetworkInterface. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetTcpipUseBootProtocol.name: mltNetTcpipUseBootProtocol
mltNetTcpipUseBootProtocol.description: Specifies the IP address acquisition method of NetworkInterface. The value taken by default depends on the implementation of a model. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetTcpipBootProtocolEnable.name: mltNetTcpipBootProtocolEnable
mltNetTcpipBootProtocolEnable.description: Bitmap for specifying BootProtocol used in order to determine the IP address of NetworkInterface. The value that should have by Default depends on the implementation of a model. An integer bitmap value specifying bootProtocols. Each bit in the integer is defined as follows. bit Value Type --- ----- --------- 0 1 Arp & Ping 1 2 RARP 2 4 BootP 3 8 DHCP 4 16 AutoIP If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetTcpipAddressServer.name: mltNetTcpipAddressServer
mltNetTcpipAddressServer.description: IP address of Server which offered IP address when IP address was acquired by bootProtocol. When it is manually inputted or Address in NVRAM is used, '0.0.0.0' shall be inputted for this value. This value shall be held even if turning a power supply off.

mltNetTcpipRawPortNumber.name: mltNetTcpipRawPortNumber
mltNetTcpipRawPortNumber.description: Port number for RAW socket printing. Default shall be '9100'. In addition, two or more RAW Port printings shall not be supported. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetTcpipSupportService.name: mltNetTcpipSupportService
mltNetTcpipSupportService.description: In NetworkInterface, shows the service supported on TCP/IP by Bitmap. An integer bitmap value specifying TCP/IP support service information. Each bit in the integer is defined as follows. bit Value Service --- ----- --------- 0 1 Reserved 1 2 Reserved 2 4 LPD 3 8 Reserved for LPR 4 16 telnet 5 32 Reserved for telnet client 6 64 ftp server 7 128 ftp client 8 256 http server 9 512 Reserved for http client 10 1024 Reserved for POP3 server 11 2048 POP3 client 12 4096 Reserved for SMTP server 13 8132 SMTP client 14 16364 ipp 15 32768 Reserved 16 65536 Reserved 17 131072 slp 18 262144 Reserved for IMAP server 19 524288 IMAP client 20 1048576 Reserved 21 2097152 Reserved for UPnP

mltNetTcpipDnsSupport.name: mltNetTcpipDnsSupport
mltNetTcpipDnsSupport.description: Sets up the availability of use of DNS. The following value shall be used. When DNS is not being supported, always takes 0. When supporting, Default shall be noUse(2). If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetTcpipDnsHostName.name: mltNetTcpipDnsHostName
mltNetTcpipDnsHostName.description: The host name of NetworkInterface used by DNS. Default in the case of supporting DNS is Null (size =0). When DNS is not being supported, implement '-' (hyphen) and shall be RO. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetTcpipDnsDomainName.name: mltNetTcpipDnsDomainName
mltNetTcpipDnsDomainName.description: Domain name to which NetworkInterface used by DNS belongs. Default in the case of supporting DNS is Null (size =0). When DNS is not being supported, implement '-' (hyphen) and shall be RO. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetTcpipDnsTable.name: mltNetTcpipDnsTable
mltNetTcpipDnsTable.description: The table for showing DNS Server.

mltNetTcpipDnsIfIndex.name: mltNetTcpipDnsIfIndex
mltNetTcpipDnsIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely showing NetworkInterface to which IP address is set. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetTcpipDnsServerIndex.name: mltNetTcpipDnsServerIndex
mltNetTcpipDnsServerIndex.description: The index for uniquely showing each DNS Server. It shall have at least one or more Indexes as Default. The number of Indexes depends on an implementation.

mltNetTcpipDnsServerAddress.name: mltNetTcpipDnsServerAddress
mltNetTcpipDnsServerAddress.description: IP address of DNS Server. If this setting can not be set from Network access, a device should implement this value with RO access.

mltNetLpdGeneralTable.name: mltNetLpdGeneralTable
mltNetLpdGeneralTable.description: The table for showing the general information of lpd.

mltNetLpdIfIndex.name: mltNetLpdIfIndex
mltNetLpdIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which lpd is set. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetLpdEnable.name: mltNetLpdEnable
mltNetLpdEnable.description: Sets up Enable/Disable of service of lpd.

mltNetLpdPort.name: mltNetLpdPort
mltNetLpdPort.description: Specifies Port number which lpd uses. Default is 515.

mltNetLpdQueueTable.name: mltNetLpdQueueTable
mltNetLpdQueueTable.description: The table for showing the information of Queue of lpd.

mltNetLpdQueueIfIndex.name: mltNetLpdQueueIfIndex
mltNetLpdQueueIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which each Queue is set. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetLpdQueueIndex.name: mltNetLpdQueueIndex
mltNetLpdQueueIndex.description: The index for uniquely showing Queue set up for every NetworkInterface. The number of Indexes depends on an implementation.

mltNetLpdQueueName.name: mltNetLpdQueueName
mltNetLpdQueueName.description: The name of Queue used at the time of printing by lpd. The value of Default depends on a model. Default shall be '-' (hyphen) when printing function has no relation to the name of Queue.

mltNetLpdQueueDescr.name: mltNetLpdQueueDescr
mltNetLpdQueueDescr.description: It recommends describing the information which serves as help when a user performs a setup for lpr printing.

mltNetLpdQueueFilter.name: mltNetLpdQueueFilter
mltNetLpdQueueFilter.description: Selects Filter function set as Queue by Bitmap. When there is no Filter function in Queue, shall always be 0. Each bit in the integer is defined as follows. bit Value Filter --- ----- --------- 0 1 FF (Form Feed) 1 2 LF (Line Feed) 2 4 CR (Carriage Return) 3 8 PS (Add PostScript Header) 4 16 reserved 5 32 rejectPS 6 64 rejectPCL 7 128 rejectASCIIt

mltNetLpdQueueBanner.name: mltNetLpdQueueBanner
mltNetLpdQueueBanner.description: A setup of BannerPage set in Queue.

mltNetLpdQueueEnable.name: mltNetLpdQueueEnable
mltNetLpdQueueEnable.description: Sets up Enable/Disable of each Queue.

mltNetFtpdGeneralTable.name: mltNetFtpdGeneralTable
mltNetFtpdGeneralTable.description: The table for showing the general information of FTP Server.

mltNetFtpdIfIndex.name: mltNetFtpdIfIndex
mltNetFtpdIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which FTP server is set up. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetFtpdEnable.name: mltNetFtpdEnable
mltNetFtpdEnable.description: Sets up Enable/Disable of service of FTP.

mltNetFtpdPort.name: mltNetFtpdPort
mltNetFtpdPort.description: Specifies Port number which FTP Server uses. Default is 21.

mltNetFtpdConfigTable.name: mltNetFtpdConfigTable
mltNetFtpdConfigTable.description: The table for showing the User information connectable to FTPServer.

mltNetFtpdConfigIfIndex.name: mltNetFtpdConfigIfIndex
mltNetFtpdConfigIfIndex.description: The Index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which each User considers as an object. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetFtpdUserIndex.name: mltNetFtpdUserIndex
mltNetFtpdUserIndex.description: The index for uniquely showing the User. The number of Indexes depends on an implementation.

mltNetFtpdUser.name: mltNetFtpdUser
mltNetFtpdUser.description: Login user name of FTP Server.

mltNetFtpdUserPassWd.name: mltNetFtpdUserPassWd
mltNetFtpdUserPassWd.description: Password of FTP Server. When it is gotten, applying scramble to value is not accepted. About security, support by the management tool side.

mltNetFtpdCapability.name: mltNetFtpdCapability
mltNetFtpdCapability.description: Shows the function permitted to each user on FTP Server by Bitmap. An integer bitmap value specifying FTP function information. Each bit in the integer is defined as follows. bit Value Filter --- ----- --------- 0 1 putting job & No Filter 1 2 putting job & CR-LF invert 2 4 get (status or job or Driver) 3 8 put NIC Firmware 4 16 put Printer Font 5 32 reserved

mltNetFtpdDescr.name: mltNetFtpdDescr
mltNetFtpdDescr.description: Explanation etc. of the function set to each user is indicated.

mltNetHttpdGeneralTable.name: mltNetHttpdGeneralTable
mltNetHttpdGeneralTable.description: The table for showing the general information about HTTP Server.

mltNetHttpdIfIndex.name: mltNetHttpdIfIndex
mltNetHttpdIfIndex.description: Index for uniquely showing NetworkInterface to which HTTP Server is set up. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetHttpdEnable.name: mltNetHttpdEnable
mltNetHttpdEnable.description: Sets up Enable/Disable of service of HTTP Server.

mltNetHttpdPort.name: mltNetHttpdPort
mltNetHttpdPort.description: The port number which HTTP Server uses. Default is 80.

mltNetHttpdDescr.name: mltNetHttpdDescr
mltNetHttpdDescr.description: Indicates the information, such as a version of HTTP Server.

mltNetSmtpGeneralTable.name: mltNetSmtpGeneralTable
mltNetSmtpGeneralTable.description: The table for showing the general information of SMTP.

mltNetSmtpIfIndex.name: mltNetSmtpIfIndex
mltNetSmtpIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which SMTP is set. The value of Index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetSmtpEnable.name: mltNetSmtpEnable
mltNetSmtpEnable.description: Sets up Enable/Disable of service of SMTP.

mltNetSmtpServerAddress.name: mltNetSmtpServerAddress
mltNetSmtpServerAddress.description: Shows the IP address of SMTP Server. Considering about specification by Domain name, it is made into DisplayString. In the case of specifying by the IP address, it shall be handled as a character string of maximum 15 characters of 'xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx'. Whether to accept a setup by Domain name is dependent on an implementation of a model.

mltNetSmtpPort.name: mltNetSmtpPort
mltNetSmtpPort.description: Specifies Port number which SMTP uses. Default is 25.

mltNetSmtpAccountTable.name: mltNetSmtpAccountTable
mltNetSmtpAccountTable.description: The table for showing Account information of SMTP.

mltNetSmtpAccountIfIndex.name: mltNetSmtpAccountIfIndex
mltNetSmtpAccountIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which each From setup makes into the object. The value of Index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetSmtpAccountIndex.name: mltNetSmtpAccountIndex
mltNetSmtpAccountIndex.description: The index for uniquely showing e-mail From address setup. Although the number of index depends on an implementation, index of the number of functions in which EP-NET and Scan function etc. are supporting needs to be prepared in Default.

mltNetSmtpFromAddress.name: mltNetSmtpFromAddress
mltNetSmtpFromAddress.description: The address of From Field used by SMTP.

mltNetSmtpReplyAddress.name: mltNetSmtpReplyAddress
mltNetSmtpReplyAddress.description: The address of RepryTo used by SMTP.

mltNetSmtpConnTimeout.name: mltNetSmtpConnTimeout
mltNetSmtpConnTimeout.description: Timeout setup in SMTP. A unit is second. It shall be possible to set the number between 30-300. Default is 60 (seconds).

mltNetSmtpPurpose.name: mltNetSmtpPurpose
mltNetSmtpPurpose.description: Displays the use of From setup of SMTP.

mltNetSmtpDescription.name: mltNetSmtpDescription
mltNetSmtpDescription.description: Description of each From setup. Default is dependent on an implementation.

mltNetIppGeneralTable.name: mltNetIppGeneralTable
mltNetIppGeneralTable.description: The table for showing the general information of IPP.

mltNetIppGeneralIfIndex.name: mltNetIppGeneralIfIndex
mltNetIppGeneralIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which IPP is set. The value of Index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetIppServiceEnable.name: mltNetIppServiceEnable
mltNetIppServiceEnable.description: Sets up Enable/Disable of service of IPP

mltNetIppDefaultPortIndex.name: mltNetIppDefaultPortIndex
mltNetIppDefaultPortIndex.description: mltNetIppPortIndex which shows Default Port number used by IPP.

mltNetIppPortTable.name: mltNetIppPortTable
mltNetIppPortTable.description: The table for showing Port information of IPP.

mltNetIppPortIfIndex.name: mltNetIppPortIfIndex
mltNetIppPortIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which IPP is set. The value of Index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltNetIppPortIndex.name: mltNetIppPortIndex
mltNetIppPortIndex.description: The index for uniquely showing Port.

mltNetIppPortNumber.name: mltNetIppPortNumber
mltNetIppPortNumber.description: Port number. '631' is supported at least.

mltNetIppPrtDescGeneralTable.name: mltNetIppPrtDescGeneralTable
mltNetIppPrtDescGeneralTable.description: The table for showing the general information about Printer Description Attribute of IPP.

mltIppPrtDescGeneralIfIndex.name: mltIppPrtDescGeneralIfIndex
mltIppPrtDescGeneralIfIndex.description: Index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which IPP is set. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltIppUriSupportedTable.name: mltIppUriSupportedTable
mltIppUriSupportedTable.description: The table for showing 'printer-uri-authentication-supported' and 'printer-uri-security-supported' to 'printer-uri-supported' attribute and each 'printer-uri'.

mltIppUriIfIndex.name: mltIppUriIfIndex
mltIppUriIfIndex.description: Index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which IPP is set. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltIppUriAuthentication.name: mltIppUriAuthentication
mltIppUriAuthentication.description: 'printer-uri-authentication' to 'printer-uri' to support is shown. This item is an IPP Ver1.1 support item. In implementation of IPP Ver1.0, it is not necessary to implement this item.

mltIppPrtStateReasonIfIndex.name: mltIppPrtStateReasonIfIndex
mltIppPrtStateReasonIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which IPP is set. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltIppPrinterStateReason.name: mltIppPrinterStateReason
mltIppPrinterStateReason.description: 'printer-state-reasons' attribute is shown. mltIppPrtStateReasonSuffix shows suffix of '-report', '-warning', and '-error'

mltIppPrtStateReasonSuffix.name: mltIppPrtStateReasonSuffix
mltIppPrtStateReasonSuffix.description: Three suffixes ('-report', '-warning', and '-error') of 'printer-state-reasons' attribute are shown.

mltIppVersionsSupportedTable.name: mltIppVersionsSupportedTable
mltIppVersionsSupportedTable.description: Table which shows 'ipp-versions-supported.' This item is an IPP Ver1.1 support item. In implementation of IPP Ver1.0, it is not necessary to implement this item.

mltIppVersionIfIndex.name: mltIppVersionIfIndex
mltIppVersionIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which IPP is set. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltIppOperationIfIndex.name: mltIppOperationIfIndex
mltIppOperationIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which IPP is set. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltIppCharSetIfIndex.name: mltIppCharSetIfIndex
mltIppCharSetIfIndex.description: The index for uniquely specifying NetworkInterface to which IPP is set. The value of index shall be the same value with mltNetGeneralIndex (ifIndex).

mltIppCharSetName.name: mltIppCharSetName
mltIppCharSetName.description: A parameter should follow regulation of IANA of the following. http://www.iana.org/assignments/character-set

mltIppCharSetCode.name: mltIppCharSetCode
mltIppCharSetCode.description: The code of 'charset' to support A parameter should follow regulation of IANA of the following. http://www.iana.org/assignments/character-set

mltIppNaturalLangIfIndex.name: mltIppNaturalLangIfIndex

mltJmMibVersion.name: mltJmMibVersion
mltJmMibVersion.description: The standardization version of MIB implemented in JobManagement relation. This indicates the version of the Private Job Management MIB that is implemented. There are some mib objects that indicate the Mib Version. (mltSysMibVersion, mltPrtMibVersion, mltScnMibVersion, mltNetMiIbVersion, mltJmMibVersion) But, the each mib version should be same version. Especially, the each major versions must be same. The version information of Standard MIB specification. General form is AA.BC. AA is indicating major revision, and B and C is minor revision. Decimal point is ASCII-coded period.

mltJmGeneralTable.name: mltJmGeneralTable
mltJmGeneralTable.description: This table indicates the general information about Job Management. This table contains the number of active jobs, oldest/newest jobs, the number of preservation of a history, and so on.

mltJmGeneralJobSetIndex.name: mltJmGeneralJobSetIndex
mltJmGeneralJobSetIndex.description: A unique value for each job set in this MIB. JobSet shows the system of the serial number used for Job management. In managing a serial number to 1 by all the functions of a device according to 'Job management standard specifications', it sets the number of JobSets to 1. In managing a serial number for every functional classification, only the number of functional classifications shall have JobSet.

mltJmGeneralNumberOfActiveJobs.name: mltJmGeneralNumberOfActiveJobs
mltJmGeneralNumberOfActiveJobs.description: The current number of 'active' jobs in the mltJmJobTable. when the device has no active jobs, this value should be 0. The device that cannot support to count active jobs should implement (-2) as fixed value.

mltJmGeneralOldestActiveJobIndex.name: mltJmGeneralOldestActiveJobIndex
mltJmGeneralOldestActiveJobIndex.description: The mltJmJobIndex of the oldest job that is still in one of the 'active' states. In other words, the index of the 'active' job that has been in the job tables the longest. If there are no active jobs, this value should be 0. The device that cannot support to count active jobs should implement (-2) as fixed value.

mltJmGeneralNewestActiveJobIndex.name: mltJmGeneralNewestActiveJobIndex
mltJmGeneralNewestActiveJobIndex.description: The mltJmJobIndex of the newest job that is in one of the 'active' states. In other words, the index of the 'active' job that has been most recently added to the job tables. If there are no active jobs, this value should be 0. The device that cannot support to count active jobs should implement (-2) as fixed value.

mltJmGeneralJobPersistence.name: mltJmGeneralJobPersistence
mltJmGeneralJobPersistence.description: The number holding the information (Index) on Job is specified after an end of Job. About the number which should hold the history information on Job, it shall be dependent on implementation of a model. If a device can not support this, '-2'(Not Support) should be implemented.

mltJmJobTable.name: mltJmJobTable
mltJmJobTable.description: The table indicates the detailed information of jobs.

mltJmJobJobSetIndex.name: mltJmJobJobSetIndex
mltJmJobJobSetIndex.description: A unique value for each job set in this MIB. JobSet shows the system of the serial number used for Job management. This index is the same as mltJmGeneralJobSetIndex.

mltJmJobIndex.name: mltJmJobIndex
mltJmJobIndex.description: The sequential, monotonously increasing identifier index for the job generated by the device when that device accepted the job. [ This Index shall hold also in power supply On./Off. After attainment is automatically re-started from 1 to maximum.

mltJmJobFunction.name: mltJmJobFunction
mltJmJobFunction.description: This value indicates the function of job sender. receiveJob(3) may include FAX and iFAX jobs.

mltJmJobStatus.name: mltJmJobStatus
mltJmJobStatus.description: This value indicates the status of job.

mltJmJobReceivedTime.name: mltJmJobReceivedTime
mltJmJobReceivedTime.description: Registration time of Job. About TimeZone, it is not indispensable. When you cannot perform acquisition of time information, be referred to as Null (Zero-Length).

mltJmJobCompleteTime.name: mltJmJobCompleteTime
mltJmJobCompleteTime.description: Completion time of Job. About TimeZone, it is not indispensable. When you await and completion time cannot be written by Job etc., be referred to as Null (Zero-Length).

mltJmJobPriority.name: mltJmJobPriority
mltJmJobPriority.description: It is used when controlling the priority of Job. When device cannot support to change of a priority, this value should be notSupported (0) as RO. When device support to change of a priority, it uses the value of 1 to 5. In this case, implementation as RW is mandatory.

mltJmJobDivNumber.name: mltJmJobDivNumber
mltJmJobDivNumber.description: The division number of job. 0-999 is used. When the device does not perform division control, this value should be (-2). (-2) means unknown.

mltJmJobOwner.name: mltJmJobOwner
mltJmJobOwner.description: The owner of job. If device cannot detect the name of owner , this value should be '-', of 'unknown'. The implementation of zero-length is not accepted.

mltJmJobType.name: mltJmJobType
mltJmJobType.description: The type of job. When the job type is not detected, this value should be other(0).

mltJmJobName.name: mltJmJobName
mltJmJobName.description: The name of job. If device cannot detect job name, this value should be '-', of 'unknown'. The implementation of zero-length is not accepted.

mltJmJobDocPageNumbers.name: mltJmJobDocPageNumbers
mltJmJobDocPageNumbers.description: The page numbers of job. When device cannot detect page numbers this value should be (-2).

mltJmJobDocCopyNumbers.name: mltJmJobDocCopyNumbers
mltJmJobDocCopyNumbers.description: Number of copies of Job. When device cannot detect the number of copies, this value should be (-2).

mltJmJobPageSize.name: mltJmJobPageSize
mltJmJobPageSize.description: The paper/picture size of Job. In case of output job, this value shows output paper size. Incase of scanned job, this value shows the size of picture. In Job of mixed size, the last page should be displayed.

mltJmJobDestination.name: mltJmJobDestination
mltJmJobDestination.description: The destination of job. If destination is unknown, this value should be '-'.

mltJmJobDataSize.name: mltJmJobDataSize
mltJmJobDataSize.description: The data size of job. A unit is KByte. In case of printing job, this value should be the size of printing date. In case of send job, this value should be not the size of picture but the size of transefered data. When the device cannot detect data size, this value should be (-2).

mltJmJobXResolution.name: mltJmJobXResolution
mltJmJobXResolution.description: Resolution of the X direction of Job. A unit is dpi.

mltJmJobYResolution.name: mltJmJobYResolution
mltJmJobYResolution.description: Resolution of the Y direction of Job. A unit is dpi.

mltJmJobOutputPages.name: mltJmJobOutputPages
mltJmJobOutputPages.description: The page numbers which the output ended in Job. If a device can not recognize this information, '-2'(Not Support) should be implemented.

mltJmJobOutputSheets.name: mltJmJobOutputSheets
mltJmJobOutputSheets.description: The sheets numbers which the output ended in Job. If a device can not recognize this information, '-2'(Not Support) should be implemented.

mltJmReportTable.name: mltJmReportTable
mltJmReportTable.description: Table for setting up the report of job history management information. If a device does not support all this functions, this table needs not to be implemented.

mltJmReportIndex.name: mltJmReportIndex
mltJmReportIndex.description: A unique value for each report destinations.

mltJmKeepAliveCount.name: mltJmKeepAliveCount
mltJmKeepAliveCount.description: The counter that controls existence of transmission to Job history information. Default shall set to 0 and, in 0, it shall not transmit to the specified address. A positive number is set when demanding transmission of Job history information. Transmission will be stopped, if it subtracts every 1 and is set to 0, whenever this counter will pass on the 1st. The side that demands transmission of Job history information makes transmission continue by rewriting this counter periodically. Moreover, when E-mail environment is not ready (grade to which the SMTP server is not set), display -1. When there is no transmitting control function, this value should be -3.

mltJmReportInterval.name: mltJmReportInterval
mltJmReportInterval.description: The number of cases that transmits Job history at once is set up.

mltJmReporIntervalSelection.name: mltJmReporIntervalSelection
mltJmReporIntervalSelection.description: The maximum of the number of cases to which once transmits Job history is shown.

mltJmReportRequest.name: mltJmReportRequest
mltJmReportRequest.description: The request command of reporting job history. default : 0 send request : 1
